  "text": "Then, heterozygous males were crossed with females homozygous for Cre recombinase driven by the cathepsin K promoter (Ctsk-Cre) [CITATION_1] . The resulting mice carry an osteoclast-specific Snx10 allele with exons 4 and 5 deleted, and therefore a null allele, which we designate Snx10 OC-. Snx10 OC-/OC-homozygous animals are hereafter referred to as \"Snx10 OC KO\", for osteoclast knockout.",
